1
00:01:31,410 --> 00:01:34,048
=The Glamorous Night=

2
00:01:34,844 --> 00:01:35,805
(Three years ago)
Vermicelli roll, please.

3
00:01:36,044 --> 00:01:37,445
- Me, too.
- A beer, thanks.

4
00:01:37,645 --> 00:01:38,568
Just a moment.

5
00:01:39,005 --> 00:01:39,764
Coming.

6
00:01:39,764 --> 00:01:41,044
Is this Vermicelli roll mine?

7
00:01:41,044 --> 00:01:41,725
Yes, yes.

8
00:01:41,800 --> 00:01:42,664
Okay, thanks.

9
00:01:42,664 --> 00:01:44,124
This one's yours.

10
00:01:44,484 --> 00:01:45,124
Here.

11
00:01:45,284 --> 00:01:45,924
Boss.

12
00:01:46,124 --> 00:01:47,924
I'll have the fifteen-yuan wontons.

13
00:01:47,924 --> 00:01:49,256
Alright.

14
00:01:50,044 --> 00:01:51,404
Is this barbecued pork mine?

15
00:01:52,005 --> 00:01:53,365
Almost ready. In a moment.

16
00:01:53,805 --> 00:01:54,525
Here you go.

17
00:02:06,204 --> 00:02:07,645
Let's switch spots, thanks.

18
00:02:28,724 --> 00:02:29,884
Watch where you're going!

19
00:02:30,604 --> 00:02:31,325
Sorry about that.

20
00:02:31,720 --> 00:02:32,325
It's fine.

21
00:02:34,444 --> 00:02:35,124
Look at that.

22
00:02:36,205 --> 00:02:36,684
See?

23
00:02:37,284 --> 00:02:39,564
We're the only two
wearing suits in this whole line.

24
00:02:46,604 --> 00:02:47,765
Just to get a bite of this,

25
00:02:48,004 --> 00:02:49,844
I specifically set an alarm
and woke up early.

26
00:02:50,004 --> 00:02:50,604
You too?

27
00:02:51,965 --> 00:02:53,724
I didn't just wake up. I didn't sleep.

28
00:02:54,604 --> 00:02:55,245
What?

29
00:02:59,805 --> 00:03:02,645
So you start work every afternoon

30
00:03:02,645 --> 00:03:04,245
and work until midnight?

31
00:03:05,444 --> 00:03:06,004
Yeah.

32
00:03:06,884 --> 00:03:08,404
Not sure how you can date anyone.

33
00:03:11,645 --> 00:03:12,684
Why so many questions?

34
00:03:14,965 --> 00:03:16,085
I'm just curious.

35
00:03:18,365 --> 00:03:19,604
Actually, you're right.

36
00:03:19,805 --> 00:03:21,444
I had a boyfriend for quite a while.

37
00:03:22,085 --> 00:03:23,684
But we still broke up in the end.

38
00:03:24,164 --> 00:03:24,884
Why?

39
00:03:25,365 --> 00:03:28,365
He always complained,
"I've never seen a woman

40
00:03:28,365 --> 00:03:30,884
drunk three hundred days a year."

41
00:03:32,884 --> 00:03:34,245
Was he your only ex?

42
00:03:36,564 --> 00:03:38,525
Seriously,
besides prying into my love life,

43
00:03:38,525 --> 00:03:39,965
don't you have anything better?

44
00:03:42,085 --> 00:03:43,844
Don't you have a morning meeting?

45
00:03:44,564 --> 00:03:45,284
I really gotta go.

46
00:03:45,485 --> 00:03:46,024
Bye.

47
00:03:51,925 --> 00:03:52,444
Hey.

48
00:03:53,525 --> 00:03:54,245
Would you mind

49
00:03:56,684 --> 00:03:57,485
exchanging WeChat?

50
00:04:16,965 --> 00:04:17,685
Accept my request,

51
00:04:19,085 --> 00:04:19,885
with Moments access.

52
00:04:23,016 --> 00:04:23,752
(Elite)

53
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:25,256
(Delicate)

54
00:04:25,256 --> 00:04:25,800
(Selfish)

55
00:04:27,304 --> 00:04:28,200
(Backstabbing)

56
00:04:29,224 --> 00:04:30,924
=Episode 4=
(The Perfect Husband)

57
00:04:30,924 --> 00:04:32,136
Why blame the company?

58
00:04:32,136 --> 00:04:33,765
Who do you think you are?

59
00:04:35,205 --> 00:04:36,804
I knew the company would be furious.

60
00:04:37,005 --> 00:04:38,085
That's why I resigned.

61
00:04:39,724 --> 00:04:41,005
Does that solve everything?

62
00:04:41,565 --> 00:04:42,376
Didn't I tell you

63
00:04:42,376 --> 00:04:43,724
I was pitching to your company?

64
00:04:43,885 --> 00:04:45,924
We were signing the contract this week,
but now,

65
00:04:45,924 --> 00:04:47,044
how do I face them?

66
00:04:48,445 --> 00:04:49,164
I'm sorry.

67
00:04:50,364 --> 00:04:52,484
Let's go celebrate first.
I'll explain on the way.

68
00:04:52,484 --> 00:04:53,645
Explain what?

69
00:04:53,765 --> 00:04:55,885
You felt cornered at the company,

70
00:04:56,364 --> 00:04:58,724
so you decided to burn everything down.

71
00:04:58,724 --> 00:05:00,104
That's not it.

72
00:05:00,765 --> 00:05:02,472
I wanted to fight back.

73
00:05:02,844 --> 00:05:04,712
I publicly demanded a promotion,

74
00:05:04,712 --> 00:05:05,352
but it failed.

75
00:05:05,352 --> 00:05:06,885
Qi Youlan's determined to fire me.

76
00:05:06,885 --> 00:05:08,844
Then I thought
about what card I could play

77
00:05:08,844 --> 00:05:10,484
to truly hurt them.

78
00:05:10,484 --> 00:05:12,164
So I thought of the sales conference.

79
00:05:12,164 --> 00:05:13,565
They care about reputation, right?

80
00:05:13,645 --> 00:05:16,445
So I made them lose face
without allowing them to complain.

81
00:05:16,484 --> 00:05:17,844
I said negotiate through pressure,

82
00:05:17,844 --> 00:05:19,885
not to attack wildly like this!

83
00:05:19,885 --> 00:05:22,364
You just blew up my entire project!

84
00:05:22,765 --> 00:05:24,645
Fine. Even if attacking was necessary,

85
00:05:24,924 --> 00:05:27,005
couldn't you have discussed it with me?

86
00:05:27,164 --> 00:05:28,364
I considered talking to you,

87
00:05:30,765 --> 00:05:32,284
but I knew you'd object.

88
00:05:34,484 --> 00:05:36,872
So, you knew I'd disagree,

89
00:05:36,872 --> 00:05:38,404
yet you still did it, didn't you?

90
00:05:40,525 --> 00:05:41,284
Yes.

91
00:05:42,604 --> 00:05:45,284
Even if you knew it'd hurt me?

92
00:05:45,965 --> 00:05:46,765
Yes.

93
00:05:48,284 --> 00:05:50,604
The quarterly sales promoter conference

94
00:05:51,844 --> 00:05:54,044
was my only shot.

95
00:05:54,404 --> 00:05:56,325
You call that a shot?

96
00:05:56,525 --> 00:05:57,325
Listen.

97
00:05:57,325 --> 00:05:59,604
Professionally speaking,
knowing your company,

98
00:05:59,604 --> 00:06:01,844
your strategy and resilience
throughout the whole thing

99
00:06:01,844 --> 00:06:03,404
were subpar.

100
00:06:03,525 --> 00:06:05,844
If I were your boss,
I wouldn't promote you either.

101
00:06:06,044 --> 00:06:08,525
You lack senior management qualities.

102
00:06:09,205 --> 00:06:12,085
To think I foolishly vouched for you
in front of Barry.

103
00:06:12,085 --> 00:06:13,284
How ridiculous of me.

104
00:06:17,164 --> 00:06:18,844
Apologize publicly to your company.

105
00:06:19,325 --> 00:06:21,085
I'll try to set up a meeting

106
00:06:21,085 --> 00:06:22,724
for you with Barry.

107
00:06:25,525 --> 00:06:26,125
No way.

108
00:06:26,404 --> 00:06:27,364
(I'm Li Dongming.)

109
00:06:27,724 --> 00:06:29,928
- (Senior Partner at Ruijin Consulting,)
- Impossible.

110
00:06:29,928 --> 00:06:32,565
- (a top HR expert in the industry)
- I'll never apologize to them.

111
00:06:32,965 --> 00:06:34,844
(and a top corporate
management consultant.)

112
00:06:35,364 --> 00:06:36,164
(But right now,)

113
00:06:37,044 --> 00:06:38,885
(I am just a husband
driven mad with rage.)

114
00:06:39,284 --> 00:06:41,885
(I've played with hawks all my life,
but I got pecked in the eye.)

115
00:06:42,604 --> 00:06:45,484
(Searching my conscience,
I treated Zhao Mei very well.)

116
00:06:46,044 --> 00:06:48,325
(I'm not like those petty,
small-minded men.)

117
00:06:48,724 --> 00:06:50,844
(I don't mind Zhao Mei's
professional success.)

118
00:06:51,244 --> 00:06:53,965
(In fact, I've always been teaching her,
mentoring her,)

119
00:06:53,965 --> 00:06:55,364
(and helping her climb the ladder.)

120
00:06:55,885 --> 00:06:57,244
(But I never imagined)

121
00:06:57,804 --> 00:07:00,005
(that she would use
the tactics I taught her)

122
00:07:00,404 --> 00:07:02,005
(to stab me in the back.)

123
00:07:02,604 --> 00:07:04,404
(That is something
I simply cannot accept.)

124
00:07:07,445 --> 00:07:07,924
Mr. Li.

125
00:07:09,284 --> 00:07:09,965
Where is Mrs. Li?

126
00:07:11,164 --> 00:07:11,724
Not coming.

127
00:07:12,484 --> 00:07:14,004
GST just called

128
00:07:14,152 --> 00:07:15,525
and canceled the meeting tomorrow.

129
00:07:18,765 --> 00:07:19,724
All the partners here?

130
00:07:20,364 --> 00:07:22,445
Yes, they're waiting for you
in the conference room.

131
00:07:24,645 --> 00:07:26,284
Sorry for keeping everyone waiting.

132
00:07:26,645 --> 00:07:28,044
Let's welcome the guest of honor.

133
00:07:30,404 --> 00:07:31,284
Come on, come on.

134
00:07:33,205 --> 00:07:36,085
This guy is highly capable
and charismatic,

135
00:07:36,085 --> 00:07:38,044
especially popular with the ladies.

136
00:07:38,044 --> 00:07:39,284
I won't dwell on those points.

137
00:07:39,525 --> 00:07:40,525
Let me just say this.

138
00:07:40,844 --> 00:07:43,525
Why was he able to receive this

139
00:07:43,724 --> 00:07:46,525
(Congratulations, Li Dongming)
unique, one-of-a-kind President's Award?

140
00:07:48,724 --> 00:07:49,965
This goes back

141
00:07:50,284 --> 00:07:53,445
to the spring seventeen years ago.

142
00:07:54,044 --> 00:07:54,765
Seventeen years?

143
00:07:56,325 --> 00:07:56,995
Seventeen years.

144
00:07:56,995 --> 00:07:58,376
On my first day,

145
00:07:58,440 --> 00:08:01,325
he was the first to greet me.

146
00:08:02,404 --> 00:08:04,484
He said, "Hello.

147
00:08:04,604 --> 00:08:05,724
My name is Li Dongming.

148
00:08:06,484 --> 00:08:08,565
Starting today, we are colleagues."

149
00:08:09,645 --> 00:08:11,565
I said, "Hello, I'm Xiao Yang."

150
00:08:12,844 --> 00:08:15,525
I thought a simple small talk
would be the end of it.

151
00:08:15,965 --> 00:08:18,765
Unexpectedly, he stopped me and said,

152
00:08:19,325 --> 00:08:22,965
"Did you take Line 1
and come up from Exit 3?"

153
00:08:24,765 --> 00:08:26,085
I found it strange, so I said,

154
00:08:26,325 --> 00:08:28,296
"How do you know I took Line 1

155
00:08:28,296 --> 00:08:30,164
and came up from Exit 3?"

156
00:08:32,296 --> 00:08:33,165
He said,

157
00:08:34,045 --> 00:08:36,524
"Your suit jacket
has some willow catkins on it.

158
00:08:37,285 --> 00:08:38,615
Although Guangzhou is big,

159
00:08:38,984 --> 00:08:40,524
not many places have willow trees.

160
00:08:41,724 --> 00:08:43,656
Exit 3 of Line 1

161
00:08:43,656 --> 00:08:45,644
happens to have two large willow trees.

162
00:08:45,724 --> 00:08:47,784
The catkins
have been really bad these days.

163
00:08:48,085 --> 00:08:49,165
You should use Exit 4."

164
00:08:50,205 --> 00:08:51,405
I thought, well,

165
00:08:52,724 --> 00:08:53,864
if he knew so much about it,

166
00:08:53,864 --> 00:08:55,405
he must take the same route.

167
00:08:56,285 --> 00:08:58,325
Unexpectedly, he said,
"I don't take Line 1.

168
00:08:58,844 --> 00:09:00,085
I take Line 8."

169
00:09:01,085 --> 00:09:02,405
I said, "Then how did you know

170
00:09:02,405 --> 00:09:05,085
about the willow catkins
at Line 1's Exit 3?"

171
00:09:06,205 --> 00:09:08,565
He said,
"In order to get into this company,

172
00:09:09,484 --> 00:09:12,364
I spent a whole month
exploring this area."

173
00:09:13,285 --> 00:09:14,004
Incredible.

174
00:09:14,524 --> 00:09:15,565
I only found out later

175
00:09:16,325 --> 00:09:18,568
that he was the top performer

176
00:09:18,568 --> 00:09:21,165
out of three thousand candidates.

177
00:09:21,524 --> 00:09:22,844
A round of applause. Come on!

178
00:09:25,524 --> 00:09:26,764
Seventeen years ago,

179
00:09:27,764 --> 00:09:30,325
Li Dongming was Ruijin Consulting's

180
00:09:30,325 --> 00:09:32,805
number one Management Trainee in China.

181
00:09:33,484 --> 00:09:36,205
Seventeen years later,
he is again Ruijin Consulting's

182
00:09:36,285 --> 00:09:39,764
number one global partner

183
00:09:39,764 --> 00:09:40,364
out of 638.

184
00:09:40,965 --> 00:09:42,405
To Li Dongming!

185
00:09:42,405 --> 00:09:43,644
Come on, to Dongming!

186
00:09:43,965 --> 00:09:44,764
Thank you, everyone.

187
00:09:44,764 --> 00:09:46,085
Thank you. Thank you.

188
00:09:46,205 --> 00:09:47,325
Thank you. Thank you.

189
00:09:50,844 --> 00:09:52,604
He's made me hungry.
Let's take our seats.

190
00:09:52,724 --> 00:09:54,644
No, no, no! You must say a few words.

191
00:09:55,445 --> 00:09:56,724
Come on, let him say something.

192
00:09:56,925 --> 00:09:58,085
Say a few words.

193
00:09:59,925 --> 00:10:00,685
A few words then.

194
00:10:02,244 --> 00:10:04,244
First, I want to thank my team.

195
00:10:04,965 --> 00:10:07,004
I couldn't receive
the President's Award today

196
00:10:07,364 --> 00:10:08,965
without their support.

197
00:10:11,325 --> 00:10:12,325
How hypocritical!

198
00:10:14,484 --> 00:10:17,244
Judy, did I offend you somehow?

199
00:10:19,685 --> 00:10:20,844
No, not at all.

200
00:10:21,724 --> 00:10:23,484
But you thanked your team.

201
00:10:23,484 --> 00:10:25,484
There are only partners here.

202
00:10:25,844 --> 00:10:27,004
Where's your team?

203
00:10:33,685 --> 00:10:34,604
You're right.

204
00:10:35,244 --> 00:10:36,104
My team...

205
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:38,685
Except for two colleagues
helping out today,

206
00:10:38,844 --> 00:10:40,085
the others didn't come.

207
00:10:40,805 --> 00:10:42,484
I did extend the invitation,

208
00:10:43,004 --> 00:10:44,445
but they all turned me down.

209
00:10:44,965 --> 00:10:46,685
Because each of them

210
00:10:46,724 --> 00:10:48,965
is working overtime
on their respective projects.

211
00:10:51,004 --> 00:10:52,205
So all I can do is ensure

212
00:10:52,685 --> 00:10:55,925
that everyone's project bonus this year

213
00:10:55,925 --> 00:10:57,256
is increased

214
00:10:57,256 --> 00:10:59,272
by ten percent.

215
00:10:59,844 --> 00:11:00,685
Come on, Dongming,

216
00:11:01,085 --> 00:11:02,445
aren't you forcing the rest of us

217
00:11:02,445 --> 00:11:04,325
to give our teams raises too?

218
00:11:05,205 --> 00:11:06,205
It's so competitive.

219
00:11:08,604 --> 00:11:10,085
Many people here today

220
00:11:10,325 --> 00:11:12,524
started as entry-level analysts.

221
00:11:13,325 --> 00:11:14,925
No one understands better than us

222
00:11:15,085 --> 00:11:17,384
what entry-level analysts truly want.

223
00:11:18,364 --> 00:11:19,325
What they want

224
00:11:19,325 --> 00:11:21,565
is tangible bonuses
deposited into their accounts,

225
00:11:22,244 --> 00:11:24,045
projects that make them shine,

226
00:11:24,844 --> 00:11:26,285
networking opportunities, expertise,

227
00:11:26,925 --> 00:11:28,844
and chances for upward mobility,

228
00:11:29,484 --> 00:11:32,604
not just drinks or a meal.

229
00:11:33,205 --> 00:11:34,884
Judy, don't you agree?

230
00:11:40,364 --> 00:11:41,445
It just occurred to me

231
00:11:41,565 --> 00:11:44,205
that you, me, and Xiao Yang
all joined Ruijin the same year.

232
00:11:44,805 --> 00:11:46,805
I made Senior Partner four years ago.

233
00:11:47,045 --> 00:11:48,445
Xiao Yang made it three years ago.

234
00:11:49,205 --> 00:11:52,205
You haven't moved up
since becoming Partner five years ago.

235
00:11:53,685 --> 00:11:56,004
That's because having a child
set me back a year.

236
00:11:56,445 --> 00:11:57,965
You don't regret it, right?

237
00:11:58,484 --> 00:11:59,045
Of course not.

238
00:11:59,844 --> 00:12:01,205
It was your choice.

239
00:12:01,565 --> 00:12:04,285
Since you chose it,
accept the outcome calmly.

240
00:12:04,764 --> 00:12:07,004
You can't take your frustrations out
on others, right?

241
00:12:08,724 --> 00:12:09,844
You've got a point.

242
00:12:10,724 --> 00:12:11,844
I owe you an apology.

243
00:12:11,965 --> 00:12:13,965
I was emotional earlier.

244
00:12:14,325 --> 00:12:16,045
My nerves have been frayed lately.

245
00:12:16,565 --> 00:12:17,165
I'm sorry.

246
00:12:20,965 --> 00:12:22,085
For the TEL project,

247
00:12:22,965 --> 00:12:24,685
you skimmed an extra percent commission.

248
00:12:26,364 --> 00:12:27,244
What are you implying?

249
00:12:27,965 --> 00:12:30,644
Nothing. I want what's best for you.

250
00:12:31,524 --> 00:12:32,565
Just a reminder.

251
00:12:32,764 --> 00:12:35,165
Stop meddling in others' affairs

252
00:12:36,884 --> 00:12:37,884
and mind your business.

253
00:12:40,325 --> 00:12:41,085
Li Dongming,

254
00:12:43,325 --> 00:12:45,004
you're in no position to lecture me.

255
00:12:45,965 --> 00:12:46,615
I heard

256
00:12:46,615 --> 00:12:49,205
your wife tanked your GST project.

257
00:12:49,844 --> 00:12:51,244
Telling me to mind my own business?

258
00:12:51,604 --> 00:12:53,124
Worry about your wife first.

259
00:12:57,640 --> 00:13:00,392
(Tiande Center)

260
00:13:10,445 --> 00:13:11,004
Come in.

261
00:13:13,884 --> 00:13:14,565
Keep it open.

262
00:13:21,205 --> 00:13:21,884
What is it?

263
00:13:24,844 --> 00:13:26,685
The Wan Jialing materials you requested.

264
00:13:27,644 --> 00:13:28,124
Got it.

265
00:13:40,965 --> 00:13:42,805
Why are you giving me a long face?

266
00:13:44,325 --> 00:13:45,484
Do you also want to comment

267
00:13:45,565 --> 00:13:47,805
on how Zhao Mei
made me lose the GST project?

268
00:13:47,805 --> 00:13:49,604
I admit it. She's my wife.

269
00:13:49,724 --> 00:13:51,565
No need for outsiders to comment.

270
00:13:52,616 --> 00:13:54,965
I don't know
why the GST project fell through.

271
00:13:58,565 --> 00:13:59,524
I just thought

272
00:14:00,724 --> 00:14:02,004
you seemed upset.

273
00:14:03,165 --> 00:14:04,004
Some dessert might

274
00:14:04,965 --> 00:14:06,965
cheer you up.

275
00:14:38,604 --> 00:14:41,484
I heard the company didn't actually
need to lay people off this time.

276
00:14:41,965 --> 00:14:44,844
They're just riding the wave
to trim their own workforce.

277
00:14:45,244 --> 00:14:45,864
Exactly.

278
00:14:46,054 --> 00:14:48,484
Following the herd
with layoffs is a good deal.

279
00:14:48,604 --> 00:14:51,325
They get to ditch the lowest performers,

280
00:14:51,724 --> 00:14:54,408
scare those of us left,

281
00:14:54,604 --> 00:14:55,604
and avoid backlash.

282
00:14:55,724 --> 00:14:56,565
Tell me about it.

283
00:14:57,484 --> 00:15:00,004
We workers really have it rough.

284
00:15:00,205 --> 00:15:01,085
To the company,

285
00:15:01,205 --> 00:15:04,085
we're just disposable consumables

286
00:15:04,484 --> 00:15:05,325
just like printers.

287
00:15:06,484 --> 00:15:09,325
Anyway, I carry a voice recorder
everywhere now.

288
00:15:09,445 --> 00:15:11,724
If HR calls me in,
I turn it on beforehand.

289
00:15:12,004 --> 00:15:13,724
I want proof of whatever they say.

290
00:15:13,844 --> 00:15:14,844
Smart move.

291
00:15:14,965 --> 00:15:15,565
Let's go.

292
00:15:35,124 --> 00:15:37,205
What's wrong? You look awful.

293
00:15:39,124 --> 00:15:40,165
My stomach's bothering me.

294
00:15:40,724 --> 00:15:41,844
Maybe you should head home.

295
00:15:43,205 --> 00:15:44,205
My report is not done.

296
00:15:45,124 --> 00:15:46,484
Well, tell me if it gets worse.

297
00:16:05,085 --> 00:16:06,484
Why are you here again?

298
00:16:07,604 --> 00:16:08,965
Well, good morning to you too.

299
00:16:09,685 --> 00:16:10,805
Can't I visit?

300
00:16:10,965 --> 00:16:11,724
Of course, you can.

301
00:16:11,724 --> 00:16:13,965
But a heads-up would be nice.

302
00:16:14,124 --> 00:16:16,844
Why is Zhao Mei
sleeping in the guest room?

303
00:16:17,085 --> 00:16:19,205
Last time it was you, and now it's her.

304
00:16:19,965 --> 00:16:21,205
What's going on with you two?

305
00:16:22,685 --> 00:16:23,884
Are you having problems?

306
00:16:24,004 --> 00:16:26,484
If there's an issue,
talk it out properly.

307
00:16:27,244 --> 00:16:28,965
You can't keep sleeping apart.

308
00:16:29,484 --> 00:16:30,694
The cold shoulder

309
00:16:30,694 --> 00:16:33,124
will only make conflicts worse.

310
00:16:33,124 --> 00:16:33,644
Mom.

311
00:16:35,045 --> 00:16:37,004
I got home very late last night,

312
00:16:37,124 --> 00:16:40,045
so I slept in the guest room
to avoid disturbing Dongming.

313
00:16:41,685 --> 00:16:42,524
You're so busy.

314
00:16:48,244 --> 00:16:48,644
Well,

315
00:16:50,925 --> 00:16:53,000
hurry up and come eat.

316
00:16:53,844 --> 00:16:55,085
I've boiled eggs for you.

317
00:17:12,605 --> 00:17:13,405
Zhao Mei,

318
00:17:13,800 --> 00:17:15,804
haven't visited your parents
in a while, right?

319
00:17:16,324 --> 00:17:16,804
Yes.

320
00:17:17,324 --> 00:17:19,205
I wanted to buy
dried abalone the other day.

321
00:17:19,965 --> 00:17:21,764
Get that pickled dish Dongming likes.

322
00:17:22,165 --> 00:17:22,764
Okay.

323
00:17:23,365 --> 00:17:26,125
I wanted to buy dried abalone,
so I went to your parents' store.

324
00:17:27,804 --> 00:17:29,096
Your parents were too busy

325
00:17:29,096 --> 00:17:31,464
to even say a word.

326
00:17:32,004 --> 00:17:33,804
They've always been like that,

327
00:17:33,804 --> 00:17:35,724
working their whole lives.
They just can't stop.

328
00:17:36,804 --> 00:17:38,724
- Workaholic lives.
- Here, I got it.

329
00:17:42,324 --> 00:17:43,004
Zhao Mei.

330
00:17:43,724 --> 00:17:46,004
I saw the video of you speaking.

331
00:17:46,724 --> 00:17:47,524
You did well.

332
00:17:48,205 --> 00:17:49,160
I shared that video

333
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:50,724
in two other group chats.

334
00:17:50,845 --> 00:17:53,324
Everyone said you handled it very well.

335
00:17:53,605 --> 00:17:54,445
Thanks.

336
00:17:54,484 --> 00:17:55,324
What for?

337
00:17:55,324 --> 00:17:57,365
Good work deserves recognition.

338
00:17:57,724 --> 00:17:58,564
Here, have some eggs.

339
00:17:58,965 --> 00:18:00,724
That's what I tell my students.

340
00:18:01,004 --> 00:18:03,240
Correcting a fault
is the greatest virtue.

341
00:18:03,368 --> 00:18:04,084
Right?

342
00:18:04,324 --> 00:18:05,445
You took the initiative

343
00:18:05,445 --> 00:18:08,125
to apologize to your subordinate.

344
00:18:08,244 --> 00:18:09,064
What does it show?

345
00:18:09,264 --> 00:18:11,965
That you're broad-minded with a vision.

346
00:18:12,324 --> 00:18:15,724
Your subordinates are lucky to have

347
00:18:15,845 --> 00:18:17,324
a leader like you.

348
00:18:17,845 --> 00:18:19,208
Yeah, pretty fortunate indeed.

349
00:18:19,724 --> 00:18:21,564
I was going to collaborate
with their company.

350
00:18:21,764 --> 00:18:23,804
But just because she admitted
the company's mistake,

351
00:18:24,044 --> 00:18:25,125
the deal fell through.

352
00:18:25,165 --> 00:18:28,004
Deal's off? So be it.

353
00:18:28,004 --> 00:18:30,284
Zhao Mei wasn't wrong, was she?

354
00:18:30,484 --> 00:18:31,524
Besides,

355
00:18:32,284 --> 00:18:34,405
speaking truth often requires sacrifice.

356
00:18:34,405 --> 00:18:37,044
Zhao Mei, you did the right thing.

357
00:18:37,044 --> 00:18:38,365
Would her absence ruin the world

358
00:18:38,365 --> 00:18:40,392
or make them not function properly?

359
00:18:40,645 --> 00:18:42,284
What a joke. Right?

360
00:18:42,724 --> 00:18:44,564
Fine. Enjoy your luck then.

361
00:18:44,564 --> 00:18:45,205
I'm off to work.

362
00:18:45,205 --> 00:18:46,244
What about your breakfast?

363
00:18:46,965 --> 00:18:49,205
Watch your tone.
Who do you think you're talking to?

364
00:18:49,885 --> 00:18:50,925
This kid.

365
00:18:51,445 --> 00:18:53,445
Yes, the rent is a bit steep,

366
00:18:53,445 --> 00:18:54,965
but look at this location.

367
00:18:55,484 --> 00:18:57,405
Surrounded by water on three sides.

368
00:18:57,564 --> 00:19:00,244
I believe its feng shui
is the best in Guangzhou.

369
00:19:00,724 --> 00:19:03,324
Renting here also showcases
our company's stature.

370
00:19:04,125 --> 00:19:06,764
That's superstition.
What matters is performance.

371
00:19:11,244 --> 00:19:12,804
It's the office lease renewal.

372
00:19:13,405 --> 00:19:14,484
Everyone's waiting on you.

373
00:19:17,244 --> 00:19:18,685
Dongming's zoning out.

374
00:19:19,925 --> 00:19:22,804
What a rare sight.
Haven't been resting well lately?

375
00:19:23,764 --> 00:19:25,845
It's not that he's not resting well.

376
00:19:26,445 --> 00:19:28,125
He's got troubles on his mind.

377
00:19:29,645 --> 00:19:30,760
Fire in the backyard.

378
00:19:31,688 --> 00:19:32,685
The front gate suffers.

379
00:19:35,004 --> 00:19:36,685
That's just how Zhang Jianyue is.

380
00:19:38,645 --> 00:19:41,445
If he's doing well,
he won't let anyone else be happy.

381
00:19:41,764 --> 00:19:44,360
When he heard you lost the GST project,
he was over the moon.

382
00:19:44,965 --> 00:19:47,925
Tell you what. I'll find a place,
and we'll have a good drink tonight

383
00:19:47,965 --> 00:19:49,125
and forget all this.

384
00:19:49,804 --> 00:19:50,524
No, thank you.

385
00:19:52,804 --> 00:19:55,205
I have a dinner appointment
with that chain store

386
00:19:55,724 --> 00:19:57,284
second-gen entrepreneur

387
00:19:57,764 --> 00:19:58,804
from Everyday Spa.

388
00:19:58,885 --> 00:19:59,484
Hold on.

389
00:20:00,405 --> 00:20:01,165
What happened?

390
00:20:02,004 --> 00:20:03,484
Even flies look like meat to you now?

391
00:20:03,724 --> 00:20:04,804
I need to hit my targets.

392
00:20:08,724 --> 00:20:09,992
Life's tough.

393
00:20:10,824 --> 00:20:12,084
You're all blinded by money.

394
00:20:13,804 --> 00:20:16,524
What's wrong with me
not liking nightclubs?

395
00:20:17,284 --> 00:20:19,764
Those private clubs, KTV rooms,

396
00:20:19,764 --> 00:20:20,685
nightclubs,

397
00:20:20,685 --> 00:20:22,284
they're so tacky and lowbrow.

398
00:20:22,284 --> 00:20:25,205
I bet only my dad's generation
enjoys those places.

399
00:20:25,445 --> 00:20:27,205
Tell me how to do business like that?

400
00:20:27,244 --> 00:20:28,764
Before discussing anything,

401
00:20:29,724 --> 00:20:31,324
tens of thousands of alcohol was downed.

402
00:20:31,484 --> 00:20:33,084
Do you think that makes sense?

403
00:20:34,365 --> 00:20:35,925
Each generation has its own way.

404
00:20:37,284 --> 00:20:38,445
That's the generation gap.

405
00:20:38,724 --> 00:20:41,645
If it were my dad,
he'd never go to some consulting firm.

406
00:20:41,645 --> 00:20:43,165
Spend millions just to buy opinions?

407
00:20:44,205 --> 00:20:45,685
He'd think that's insane.

408
00:20:48,205 --> 00:20:51,004
It has been over half a month

409
00:20:52,004 --> 00:20:53,004
since our last meeting.

410
00:20:53,125 --> 00:20:55,445
How come there's still no follow-up?

411
00:20:57,484 --> 00:20:59,405
I have never seen
a vendor be picky on clients.

412
00:21:00,484 --> 00:21:02,632
Mr. Qin, about last time...

413
00:21:02,632 --> 00:21:03,524
Please let me explain.

414
00:21:03,524 --> 00:21:06,445
Our research requires
data analysis and data support.

415
00:21:06,445 --> 00:21:08,205
So it naturally takes a bit longer.

416
00:21:08,724 --> 00:21:09,524
Buddy.

417
00:21:10,365 --> 00:21:11,685
For real?

418
00:21:11,965 --> 00:21:13,764
Has your dad also lost his mind?

419
00:21:13,764 --> 00:21:15,484
Wait, tell me quickly. What's going on?

420
00:21:16,965 --> 00:21:18,165
That recent video online...

421
00:21:18,165 --> 00:21:21,885
Nowadays, none of these nepobabies
knows how to talk properly, huh?

422
00:21:22,165 --> 00:21:23,484
So hard to please.

423
00:21:23,724 --> 00:21:24,324
I heard that.

424
00:21:26,125 --> 00:21:27,044
So whose fault is it?

425
00:21:28,165 --> 00:21:29,004
Let me handle this.

426
00:21:30,125 --> 00:21:31,205
It's the company's fault.

427
00:21:31,205 --> 00:21:33,645
Look, this woman speaks really well.

428
00:21:33,764 --> 00:21:35,205
So cool.

429
00:21:35,205 --> 00:21:36,324
Share this with me.

430
00:21:39,965 --> 00:21:42,284
Fang, what's up?
You called so many times.

431
00:21:45,165 --> 00:21:47,284
Yeah, Barry is going to play golf?

432
00:21:48,445 --> 00:21:50,084
Great! Send me his tea time right away.

433
00:21:51,484 --> 00:21:52,605
You'll be rewarded.

434
00:21:53,405 --> 00:21:54,845
Of course. Transferring it now.

435
00:21:56,284 --> 00:21:57,965
Mr. Li, what's the matter?

436
00:21:58,120 --> 00:22:00,125
Barry will play golf
with his girlfriend tomorrow.

437
00:22:00,125 --> 00:22:00,845
That's good news.

438
00:22:01,405 --> 00:22:03,764
We'll intercept him
at the golf course tomorrow morning.

439
00:22:03,764 --> 00:22:04,484
Good point.

440
00:22:08,205 --> 00:22:09,724
He's going with his girlfriend.

441
00:22:13,044 --> 00:22:13,925
I don't need you.

442
00:22:17,764 --> 00:22:19,004
I need a girl.

443
00:22:19,208 --> 00:22:22,152
(Medicine)

444
00:22:33,244 --> 00:22:33,965
Room 401.

445
00:22:35,845 --> 00:22:36,564
Calling me?

446
00:22:36,804 --> 00:22:37,524
A delivery.

447
00:22:39,764 --> 00:22:40,445
There you go.

448
00:22:41,244 --> 00:22:41,965
Thanks.

449
00:22:43,324 --> 00:22:43,764
Thanks.

450
00:22:44,724 --> 00:22:45,284
Thank you.

451
00:22:46,724 --> 00:22:47,445
I got it.

452
00:22:49,965 --> 00:22:51,764
- Who is it?
- A delivery guy.

453
00:22:55,004 --> 00:22:56,165
Help me open it.

454
00:22:57,284 --> 00:22:57,965
What is this?

455
00:23:00,564 --> 00:23:02,004
Your father sent food again.

456
00:23:02,724 --> 00:23:03,496
My dad

457
00:23:04,136 --> 00:23:06,205
is always worried
that I don't eat well here.

458
00:23:07,804 --> 00:23:09,445
That's your real father.

459
00:23:10,205 --> 00:23:11,165
There's some for you.

460
00:23:11,165 --> 00:23:12,776
Thank you, sir.

461
00:23:14,044 --> 00:23:14,965
Bacon!

462
00:23:16,645 --> 00:23:18,645
Stir-frying it with garlic sprouts
is delicious.

463
00:23:19,445 --> 00:23:20,804
Too bad neither of us can cook it.

464
00:23:23,044 --> 00:23:25,764
Is this bacon raw or cooked?

465
00:23:31,524 --> 00:23:32,205
What's wrong?

466
00:23:32,965 --> 00:23:33,965
I just spaced out.

467
00:23:35,816 --> 00:23:36,845
Because of the layoffs?

468
00:23:39,724 --> 00:23:41,445
Everyone was talking about layoffs.

469
00:23:41,645 --> 00:23:43,645
Alright, stop thinking about it.
There's no point.

470
00:23:47,165 --> 00:23:49,564
Did you see that video of the GST

471
00:23:49,564 --> 00:23:50,324
female executive?

472
00:23:50,804 --> 00:23:52,365
Her speech was quite cathartic.

473
00:23:53,564 --> 00:23:54,685
That female executive

474
00:23:55,724 --> 00:23:56,605
is Mrs. Li.

475
00:23:58,365 --> 00:23:59,524
She is Mr. Li's wife?

476
00:24:00,645 --> 00:24:01,284
How do you know?

477
00:24:04,885 --> 00:24:07,165
(Accompany me
to see a client tomorrow at 7 AM.)

478
00:24:12,104 --> 00:24:14,248
(Okay, no problem.)

479
00:24:15,885 --> 00:24:16,564
Mr. Li?

480
00:24:17,484 --> 00:24:18,244
What did he want?

481
00:24:19,004 --> 00:24:21,365
Need to accompany him
to see a client at 7 AM tomorrow.

482
00:24:22,365 --> 00:24:24,804
Meeting a client that early? Where?

483
00:24:25,885 --> 00:24:26,645
A hotel?

484
00:24:27,284 --> 00:24:28,205
Stop it.

485
00:24:28,205 --> 00:24:32,284
He said it's at the Lanbi Lake
Golf Course.

486
00:24:33,044 --> 00:24:34,004
Lanbi Lake?

487
00:24:35,125 --> 00:24:37,885
That's so far! Even taking a cab
would take two hours.

488
00:24:39,125 --> 00:24:41,084
Then I'd have to get up at five.
Wait, no.

489
00:24:42,044 --> 00:24:43,284
I'll have to get up at 4 AM.

490
00:24:43,645 --> 00:24:44,724
Gotta go. I'm sleeping now.

491
00:24:45,004 --> 00:24:46,044
Getting up at 4 AM.

492
00:24:47,645 --> 00:24:49,804
Wait, that's not right.

493
00:24:51,205 --> 00:24:52,365
Does Mr. Li like you?

494
00:24:52,925 --> 00:24:54,084
What? No.

495
00:24:54,365 --> 00:24:56,405
Stop saying nonsense. Honestly.

496
00:24:56,405 --> 00:24:57,925
Stop playing dumb.

497
00:24:58,685 --> 00:25:01,845
A male boss taking a female subordinate
to play golf?

498
00:25:02,685 --> 00:25:04,284
You're telling me you don't get it?

499
00:25:06,405 --> 00:25:07,205
I don't.

500
00:25:07,965 --> 00:25:09,764
Always talking nonsense. Really.

501
00:25:09,764 --> 00:25:11,645
A golf ball straight to your heart.

502
00:25:11,724 --> 00:25:13,324
Acting all innocent with me.

503
00:25:28,445 --> 00:25:29,205
Good morning.

504
00:25:29,205 --> 00:25:30,324
You're here. So early.

505
00:25:31,165 --> 00:25:32,004
Sorry, Mr. Li.

506
00:25:32,484 --> 00:25:34,125
I don't have golf clothes.

507
00:25:34,125 --> 00:25:35,205
They sell them inside.

508
00:25:37,484 --> 00:25:38,125
How much?

509
00:25:38,125 --> 00:25:39,244
3,890 yuan in total.

510
00:25:40,205 --> 00:25:41,044
That expensive?

511
00:25:41,724 --> 00:25:42,845
Don't worry about it.

512
00:25:43,205 --> 00:25:44,324
3,890 in total.

513
00:25:49,205 --> 00:25:50,125
Thank you, sir.

514
00:25:50,205 --> 00:25:50,764
All done.

515
00:25:50,764 --> 00:25:51,125
Okay.

516
00:25:53,885 --> 00:25:54,405
Okay.

517
00:25:54,405 --> 00:25:55,244
Thank you.

518
00:25:58,645 --> 00:26:00,685
Sorry about that. We just need a moment.

519
00:26:01,044 --> 00:26:01,925
We'll warm up first.

520
00:26:08,004 --> 00:26:09,365
Yes, keep your eyes on that grass.

521
00:26:09,724 --> 00:26:12,405
If you can hit that grass,
you can hit the ball.

522
00:26:21,605 --> 00:26:23,324
(How could I easily
give up on my project?)

523
00:26:24,004 --> 00:26:25,564
(I must make Barry understand)

524
00:26:25,965 --> 00:26:28,004
- (that Zhao Mei and I are different.)
- Let's start.

525
00:26:28,365 --> 00:26:30,324
Spread your legs apart a bit.

526
00:26:30,484 --> 00:26:31,284
Yes, open them up.

527
00:26:31,925 --> 00:26:32,724
And position

528
00:26:32,965 --> 00:26:35,284
the inner side of your left heel
towards the ball.

529
00:26:36,205 --> 00:26:37,484
Stick your butt out a little.

530
00:26:37,484 --> 00:26:38,205
Yes, like that.

531
00:26:38,205 --> 00:26:41,484
(A male boss taking a female subordinate
to play golf?)

532
00:26:42,165 --> 00:26:43,804
(You're telling me you don't get it?)

533
00:26:44,484 --> 00:26:45,685
Yes, rotate your hips.

534
00:26:46,645 --> 00:26:49,205
Right, rotate your hips.
Don't use your arms.

535
00:26:50,165 --> 00:26:50,696
Like this.

536
00:26:52,205 --> 00:26:52,764
Dongming.

537
00:26:55,244 --> 00:26:56,044
What a coincidence.

538
00:27:00,284 --> 00:27:02,965
Not a coincidence.
I came specifically to see you.

539
00:27:03,244 --> 00:27:04,044
You know,

540
00:27:04,484 --> 00:27:07,084
I've liked you
since the first time we met.

541
00:27:08,084 --> 00:27:09,484
Because you never hide anything.

542
00:27:10,724 --> 00:27:13,605
Because I know nothing
can be hidden from you.

543
00:27:14,324 --> 00:27:15,284
My girlfriend, Lisa.

544
00:27:16,004 --> 00:27:17,044
This is Li Dongming.

545
00:27:17,965 --> 00:27:18,484
Hello, Lisa.

546
00:27:18,724 --> 00:27:19,125
Hi.

547
00:27:19,764 --> 00:27:20,925
Qiao Hailun from my team.

548
00:27:22,044 --> 00:27:22,965
Mr. Barry, hello.

549
00:27:22,965 --> 00:27:23,365
Hello.

550
00:27:23,645 --> 00:27:24,044
Lisa.

551
00:27:25,205 --> 00:27:26,645
Didn't you say you like Zhao Mei?

552
00:27:27,885 --> 00:27:29,445
He's Zhao Mei's husband.

553
00:27:31,484 --> 00:27:32,484
I really like your wife.

554
00:27:32,724 --> 00:27:33,965
I find her very courageous.

555
00:27:34,405 --> 00:27:36,405
- Thank you.
- But I see things differently.

556
00:27:36,724 --> 00:27:38,205
She thinks Zhao Mei is brave.

557
00:27:38,885 --> 00:27:39,816
But I believe

558
00:27:40,712 --> 00:27:42,205
she is foolish, reckless,

559
00:27:43,445 --> 00:27:44,776
and lacks professionalism.

560
00:27:44,925 --> 00:27:45,645
Barry.

561
00:27:47,365 --> 00:27:48,284
But I still love you.

562
00:27:50,965 --> 00:27:51,764
Let's play together.

563
00:27:53,244 --> 00:27:54,925
Come on, let's tee off again.

564
00:27:55,205 --> 00:27:56,925
Hold the club looser.

565
00:27:56,925 --> 00:27:58,244
Like you're holding a whip.

566
00:27:59,445 --> 00:28:00,084
Looser grip.

567
00:28:02,605 --> 00:28:03,084
Yes.

568
00:28:03,564 --> 00:28:04,685
Good, rotate your core.

569
00:28:04,764 --> 00:28:06,405
Backswing. Keep your eye on it.

570
00:28:06,405 --> 00:28:07,445
It's a little bit...

571
00:28:07,645 --> 00:28:08,445
Downswing.

572
00:28:08,764 --> 00:28:10,885
Yes, keep your head there.
Still looking down?

573
00:28:13,484 --> 00:28:14,205
Nice shot!

574
00:28:17,165 --> 00:28:17,764
Thanks.

575
00:28:18,125 --> 00:28:18,645
Let's go.

576
00:28:20,685 --> 00:28:22,792
I bet you really like that girl.

577
00:28:25,484 --> 00:28:27,144
Asian standards for female beauty

578
00:28:27,144 --> 00:28:28,885
still favor pale and thin.

579
00:28:29,724 --> 00:28:32,165
But I, I prefer curvier women.

580
00:28:32,804 --> 00:28:35,125
Curvy women have more vitality.

581
00:28:36,645 --> 00:28:39,405
Are you saying
you're not interested in your wife?

582
00:28:40,845 --> 00:28:43,004
Zhao Mei isn't built like that.

583
00:28:43,764 --> 00:28:45,125
Although we're married,

584
00:28:45,724 --> 00:28:48,724
it doesn't mean
we're compatible in every way.

585
00:28:51,004 --> 00:28:53,925
Listen, Dongming,
I can't sign with your company.

586
00:28:54,885 --> 00:28:57,125
You're smart, and I like you a lot.

587
00:28:58,244 --> 00:29:00,328
But your wife is foolish.

588
00:29:00,584 --> 00:29:01,284
Do you get it?

589
00:29:01,965 --> 00:29:02,885
To be honest,

590
00:29:03,205 --> 00:29:05,524
I didn't realize you'd take it so hard.

591
00:29:07,165 --> 00:29:08,724
You think I shouldn't care?

592
00:29:09,244 --> 00:29:10,484
Your wife went out there

593
00:29:10,484 --> 00:29:13,685
and declared publicly that
my company's the source of all evil.

594
00:29:14,044 --> 00:29:15,244
Is she out of her mind?

595
00:29:16,764 --> 00:29:18,605
GST is a respectable company,

596
00:29:18,605 --> 00:29:20,484
and she made us look like some vulgar

597
00:29:20,524 --> 00:29:21,576
low-class little store

598
00:29:21,576 --> 00:29:23,685
that is getting slandered
on social media every day.

599
00:29:23,685 --> 00:29:25,405
Barry, I'm truly sorry.

600
00:29:26,004 --> 00:29:28,244
Is there any room for compromise?

601
00:29:28,804 --> 00:29:31,284
Personally and professionally,
I'll owe you big time.

602
00:29:31,524 --> 00:29:33,484
Unless she publicly
apologizes to the company,

603
00:29:34,125 --> 00:29:35,688
I'll sue her for defamation

604
00:29:35,945 --> 00:29:37,165
and damaging our reputation.

605
00:29:44,845 --> 00:29:45,445
Hello.

606
00:29:45,605 --> 00:29:48,405
Your green fees, caddie tips,
and meal charges

607
00:29:48,405 --> 00:29:50,685
have already been settled by Mr. Li.

608
00:29:59,284 --> 00:30:00,125
Mr. Li.

609
00:30:01,405 --> 00:30:02,484
I really admire you.

610
00:30:03,645 --> 00:30:04,645
If I were you,

611
00:30:05,284 --> 00:30:07,605
seeing a contract
that was about to close fall through,

612
00:30:08,965 --> 00:30:09,965
I'd be devastated.

613
00:30:11,165 --> 00:30:12,724
Right now, I feel so choked up

614
00:30:13,724 --> 00:30:14,764
I can't eat a thing.

615
00:30:14,885 --> 00:30:16,084
You think I came this early

616
00:30:16,244 --> 00:30:18,125
just to corner him about the project?

617
00:30:18,925 --> 00:30:19,724
Isn't that it?

618
00:30:20,845 --> 00:30:22,724
The project is only part of it.

619
00:30:24,645 --> 00:30:25,965
It's mainly because of Zhao Mei.

620
00:30:26,564 --> 00:30:28,044
She's my wife.

621
00:30:28,405 --> 00:30:29,804
Losing a client is nothing new,

622
00:30:30,484 --> 00:30:33,044
but I can't let her leave GST like this.

623
00:30:33,405 --> 00:30:35,244
I think you
expressed yourself wrong today.

624
00:30:36,205 --> 00:30:37,445
Do you also think that Zhao Mei

625
00:30:37,685 --> 00:30:39,685
admitting the company's mistake
was admirable?

626
00:30:41,645 --> 00:30:43,685
But people in the industry
don't see it that way.

627
00:30:43,965 --> 00:30:46,244
They'll see her as a troublemaker.

628
00:30:47,445 --> 00:30:49,205
I won't let GST sue her.

629
00:30:49,804 --> 00:30:50,324
Otherwise,

630
00:30:50,484 --> 00:30:53,125
her career in this industry
would be completely over.

631
00:30:53,125 --> 00:30:55,044
I will never let that happen.

632
00:30:58,205 --> 00:30:59,445
How I envy your wife,

633
00:31:00,365 --> 00:31:02,524
having an HR expert like you

634
00:31:02,925 --> 00:31:03,965
helping her out.

635
00:31:04,405 --> 00:31:07,004
Most people, like me,

636
00:31:08,044 --> 00:31:09,484
are like headless flies,

637
00:31:10,445 --> 00:31:11,365
bumping around.

638
00:31:12,004 --> 00:31:14,724
Marriage isn't easy to come by.
We all should cherish it.

639
00:31:16,004 --> 00:31:16,885
Job, too.

640
00:31:21,764 --> 00:31:23,405
You must really love your wife, right?

641
00:31:23,405 --> 00:31:26,004
Of course,
we just got married two years ago.

642
00:31:28,004 --> 00:31:28,804
To be honest,

643
00:31:29,645 --> 00:31:32,524
I never thought I'd get married
in this lifetime before.

644
00:31:33,405 --> 00:31:34,824
So what made you decide?

645
00:31:37,365 --> 00:31:38,804
My mom was pushing me back then.

646
00:31:41,965 --> 00:31:44,925
Until one time I went on a business trip
to Singapore.

647
00:31:44,925 --> 00:31:47,925
(Singapore)

648
00:31:47,925 --> 00:31:49,564
Dongming, the doctor said

649
00:31:49,845 --> 00:31:51,405
it's fulminant diabetes.

650
00:31:51,560 --> 00:31:52,965
They can't treat it here.

651
00:31:53,284 --> 00:31:55,885
I heard the Fourth Hospital
specializes in treating this.

652
00:31:55,885 --> 00:31:58,284
But it's impossible
to get an appointment there.

653
00:31:58,524 --> 00:31:59,885
I... I got it, Dad.

654
00:32:00,044 --> 00:32:01,925
Don't worry, I'll figure something out.

655
00:32:02,645 --> 00:32:03,564
Don't worry.

656
00:32:03,564 --> 00:32:04,524
- Okay.
- I have to go.

657
00:32:04,524 --> 00:32:04,845
Okay.

658
00:32:17,645 --> 00:32:18,365
Where are you?

659
00:32:18,925 --> 00:32:20,685
I'm at that Tiangong Bar.

660
00:32:21,084 --> 00:32:21,925
Are you here too?

661
00:32:22,484 --> 00:32:24,044
No, I'm not. I'm in Singapore.

662
00:32:24,724 --> 00:32:27,165
I need to ask you a favor.

663
00:32:28,804 --> 00:32:29,645
Here's the thing.

664
00:32:30,004 --> 00:32:33,205
My mom suddenly developed
fulminant diabetes.

665
00:32:34,004 --> 00:32:35,965
She needs to be admitted
to the Fourth Hospital.

666
00:32:36,965 --> 00:32:37,804
The Fourth Hospital?

667
00:32:38,445 --> 00:32:39,645
Okay, okay, I'll try.

668
00:32:40,405 --> 00:32:43,165
Send me your dad's
contact info and address.

669
00:32:43,165 --> 00:32:44,004
I'll go right now.

670
00:32:45,352 --> 00:32:46,764
(Next day, I arrived in Guangzhou)

671
00:32:46,764 --> 00:32:48,804
(and went straight to the hospital.)

672
00:32:49,244 --> 00:32:49,965
(At the ward,)

673
00:32:49,965 --> 00:32:52,764
(I saw Zhao Mei
talking quietly with the doctor.)

674
00:32:53,205 --> 00:32:56,244
(She saw me and gave me a thumbs up.)

675
00:32:56,484 --> 00:32:57,845
I felt reassured right then.

676
00:32:58,524 --> 00:33:01,244
I knew right then
I had to marry this woman.

677
00:33:02,445 --> 00:33:03,284
So romantic.

678
00:33:07,405 --> 00:33:08,885
To be honest,

679
00:33:10,244 --> 00:33:11,284
at that time,

680
00:33:11,965 --> 00:33:16,445
I still had some other emotional baggage

681
00:33:16,885 --> 00:33:19,284
dragging on unresolved.

682
00:33:20,044 --> 00:33:21,484
I hadn't thought about marriage.

683
00:33:23,205 --> 00:33:24,804
But when I found out

684
00:33:25,484 --> 00:33:26,804
my mom was sick,

685
00:33:26,804 --> 00:33:28,804
the first person I thought of
was Zhao Mei.

686
00:33:29,405 --> 00:33:31,524
But a woman
who can be a wife is different.

687
00:33:31,965 --> 00:33:33,445
You can entrust her with big things.

688
00:33:33,965 --> 00:33:36,125
Someone I can trust with my back.

689
00:33:36,965 --> 00:33:39,685
That person could only be Zhao Mei.

690
00:33:41,324 --> 00:33:42,804
If it were Zhao Mei,

691
00:33:42,952 --> 00:33:44,044
she wouldn't believe it.

692
00:33:44,044 --> 00:33:45,685
The golf course has a great environment.

693
00:33:46,365 --> 00:33:47,365
We can order some drinks.

694
00:33:47,405 --> 00:33:48,004
Danning?

695
00:33:48,445 --> 00:33:49,165
Li Dongming.

696
00:33:50,724 --> 00:33:51,885
Excuse me for a minute.

697
00:33:52,205 --> 00:33:52,605
Okay.

698
00:33:52,605 --> 00:33:53,724
See you in a bit, see you.

699
00:33:54,965 --> 00:33:56,764
You also like playing golf this early?

700
00:33:56,885 --> 00:33:58,365
I'm not here to play golf.

701
00:33:58,365 --> 00:33:59,645
It's all for work.

702
00:33:59,965 --> 00:34:00,965
Barry is inside.

703
00:34:03,845 --> 00:34:04,845
You knew he is here?

704
00:34:05,205 --> 00:34:07,724
I didn't know.
I'm just here accompanying a client.

705
00:34:08,204 --> 00:34:09,965
The big boss being here
is not my concern.

706
00:34:09,965 --> 00:34:11,204
He probably doesn't know me.

707
00:34:12,524 --> 00:34:14,524
Talk to Zhao Mei.
Tell her not to be so stubborn.

708
00:34:14,885 --> 00:34:17,124
This industry is small,
unless she wants to quit.

709
00:34:17,285 --> 00:34:18,684
I'd be willing to support her.

710
00:34:21,004 --> 00:34:22,644
Alright, I get it. I'll talk to her.

711
00:34:23,004 --> 00:34:24,684
Thank you. Have a good game.

712
00:34:34,965 --> 00:34:36,044
I'm at the golf course.

713
00:34:36,405 --> 00:34:38,484
Do you know who Barry is meeting here?

714
00:34:38,925 --> 00:34:40,044
Your husband.

715
00:35:00,008 --> 00:35:04,072
(First golf in life)

716
00:35:07,484 --> 00:35:08,204
Qiao Hailun.

717
00:35:09,684 --> 00:35:10,925
Yes, sir.

718
00:35:11,245 --> 00:35:12,365
When you get to the office,

719
00:35:12,684 --> 00:35:15,445
give me the Phase II analysis report
for the Wan Jialing project.

720
00:35:19,564 --> 00:35:22,044
Um, I still have a bit left.

721
00:35:23,325 --> 00:35:25,245
I planned to finish it this morning,

722
00:35:25,684 --> 00:35:28,325
but we ended up
playing golf this morning.

723
00:35:28,805 --> 00:35:30,765
Did you only find out
about the golf game today?

724
00:35:31,925 --> 00:35:33,484
Why didn't you finish it last night?

725
00:35:38,365 --> 00:35:39,564
I'll finish it before I leave.

726
00:35:39,885 --> 00:35:41,416
Before 3 PM.

727
00:35:42,024 --> 00:35:43,004
You must give it to me.

728
00:35:45,084 --> 00:35:45,765
Understood.

729
00:36:00,564 --> 00:36:01,445
Why is it dead?

730
00:36:09,925 --> 00:36:11,445
She's really beautiful!

731
00:36:11,725 --> 00:36:14,164
I didn't expect Mr. Li's wife
to be so pretty.

732
00:36:16,765 --> 00:36:18,604
Hailun, have you met her in person?

733
00:36:21,805 --> 00:36:22,285
Qiao Hailun.

734
00:36:24,164 --> 00:36:26,204
If you're tired,
you should go back and rest.

735
00:36:26,325 --> 00:36:28,084
It's fine to leave early for once.

736
00:36:28,644 --> 00:36:29,405
No.

737
00:36:30,164 --> 00:36:31,885
I haven't finished this research report.

738
00:36:32,365 --> 00:36:33,725
I have to submit it today.

739
00:36:35,044 --> 00:36:35,805
Got it. Got it.

740
00:36:38,885 --> 00:36:40,604
What are you looking at?
You seem thrilled.

741
00:36:41,124 --> 00:36:42,245
Here, I'll show you.

742
00:36:43,484 --> 00:36:43,925
Come on.

743
00:36:44,484 --> 00:36:45,285
What is it?

744
00:36:45,445 --> 00:36:45,925
Come over.

745
00:36:46,524 --> 00:36:47,204
Sit here.

746
00:36:48,965 --> 00:36:51,204
So? Isn't she stunning?

747
00:36:52,365 --> 00:36:53,765
Why are you looking at her photos?

748
00:36:54,965 --> 00:36:56,164
I just saw them online.

749
00:36:56,684 --> 00:36:59,124
Her old photos got dug up online.

750
00:37:00,044 --> 00:37:01,925
Let me show you one I really like.

751
00:37:02,765 --> 00:37:04,805
This one. Isn't the aura powerful?

752
00:37:06,765 --> 00:37:07,684
You admire her so?

753
00:37:09,044 --> 00:37:09,644
Not really.

754
00:37:10,845 --> 00:37:12,524
I just think she's bold
speaking her mind.

755
00:37:13,004 --> 00:37:14,524
Before, I always thought

756
00:37:14,524 --> 00:37:16,164
workplace sexual harassment

757
00:37:16,164 --> 00:37:17,644
was either the man's fault

758
00:37:17,765 --> 00:37:19,124
or the woman's.

759
00:37:19,765 --> 00:37:22,204
Now I know
it's the toxic workplace itself.

760
00:37:22,285 --> 00:37:23,845
What toxic workplace?

761
00:37:23,845 --> 00:37:24,405
Seriously.

762
00:37:25,524 --> 00:37:26,325
Frankly,

763
00:37:26,965 --> 00:37:29,725
those are just people
blaming society for all their troubles.

764
00:37:30,245 --> 00:37:31,624
Whenever they face any problem,

765
00:37:31,816 --> 00:37:33,405
they blame it on the bad market.

766
00:37:33,925 --> 00:37:36,004
What, is she some revolutionary?

767
00:37:37,044 --> 00:37:39,325
Qiao Hailun,
is that really how you see it?

768
00:37:39,845 --> 00:37:41,684
You think she's wrong, don't you?

769
00:37:45,004 --> 00:37:47,564
Whether she's right isn't my concern.

770
00:37:47,965 --> 00:37:50,925
But she completely ruined

771
00:37:50,925 --> 00:37:51,725
our GST project.

772
00:37:52,445 --> 00:37:53,285
Listen.

773
00:37:53,405 --> 00:37:56,004
Mr. Li was deeply invested in this.

774
00:37:56,245 --> 00:37:57,928
We were about to sign
the contract today.

775
00:37:58,164 --> 00:37:59,845
And now? It's all gone.

776
00:38:01,365 --> 00:38:02,564
And she's Mr. Li's wife.

777
00:38:02,765 --> 00:38:05,325
Selfish, I say.

778
00:38:05,965 --> 00:38:07,725
I never noticed

779
00:38:08,484 --> 00:38:10,325
you're so loyal to Mr. Li.

780
00:38:12,925 --> 00:38:14,824
Do you... like him?

781
00:38:14,824 --> 00:38:15,845
Don't be ridiculous.

782
00:38:16,285 --> 00:38:17,928
I feel bad for my lost bonus!

783
00:38:18,885 --> 00:38:20,564
No, you feel bad for him.

784
00:38:21,925 --> 00:38:24,644
Stop it!
I was working on that project too.

785
00:38:29,845 --> 00:38:31,204
Kidding! Just kidding!

786
00:38:31,528 --> 00:38:35,816
(Tiande Center)

787
00:38:38,965 --> 00:38:40,245
(We seem to have two brains.)

788
00:38:40,504 --> 00:38:41,245
Right here.

789
00:38:41,245 --> 00:38:43,644
- (One emotional, one rational.)
- Honestly and sincerely,

790
00:38:45,044 --> 00:38:46,124
- (Right now,)
- I apologize

791
00:38:46,885 --> 00:38:48,405
- (as I see Zhao Mei)
- to everyone.

792
00:38:48,644 --> 00:38:50,285
(making her speech,)

793
00:38:50,644 --> 00:38:52,164
(my emotional brain is telling me)

794
00:38:52,684 --> 00:38:55,084
(to strangle that self-righteous woman
on screen)

795
00:38:55,084 --> 00:38:56,405
(who ruined my payday.)

796
00:38:58,204 --> 00:39:00,124
(But my rational brain said,)

797
00:39:01,445 --> 00:39:04,325
(yes, she's despicable,)

798
00:39:05,365 --> 00:39:06,084
(but...)

799
00:39:35,285 --> 00:39:37,365
I thought you weren't
coming back tonight.

800
00:39:38,564 --> 00:39:39,285
So?

801
00:39:41,285 --> 00:39:43,885
Dressed like that,
are you going clubbing?

802
00:39:45,204 --> 00:39:46,405
No, to file a missing report.

803
00:39:47,245 --> 00:39:49,164
Someone wasn't answering their phone.

804
00:40:05,802 --> 00:40:10,542
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

805
00:40:14,992 --> 00:40:16,912
♪Too much of shame♪

806
00:40:17,258 --> 00:40:20,054
♪To waste it crying♪

807
00:40:22,512 --> 00:40:24,432
♪Leave all behind you♪

808
00:40:24,432 --> 00:40:26,712
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

809
00:40:26,832 --> 00:40:29,061
♪You know how far you've gone♪

810
00:40:29,196 --> 00:40:31,472
♪In the fire you rise again♪

811
00:40:31,658 --> 00:40:34,018
♪You made it through the worst♪

812
00:40:34,156 --> 00:40:36,360
♪The best is yet to come♪

813
00:40:36,603 --> 00:40:38,743
♪The best is yet to come♪

814
00:40:41,445 --> 00:40:42,768
♪Isn't it magical♪

815
00:40:42,768 --> 00:40:44,400
♪Listen, look,
how beautiful the night is♪

816
00:40:44,432 --> 00:40:46,899
♪With countless lights on,
is someone heartbroken again♪

817
00:40:46,899 --> 00:40:49,352
♪The sound of a heart
shattering on the ground is so crisp♪

818
00:40:49,433 --> 00:40:52,081
♪Turn on a light.
A lonely heart needs comfort♪

819
00:40:52,170 --> 00:40:54,701
♪Sweat, toil, dawn, dusk♪

820
00:40:54,781 --> 00:40:57,003
♪Devaluing self-respect
just for some hot food♪

821
00:40:57,145 --> 00:40:58,226
♪But I don't want to♪

822
00:40:58,335 --> 00:41:00,601
♪Sell dignity at a price,
trampling on past vows♪

823
00:41:00,717 --> 00:41:01,782
♪Until 3 AM♪

824
00:41:01,953 --> 00:41:03,158
♪Locking dreams away in a drawer♪

825
00:41:03,312 --> 00:41:04,545
♪Just to earn some meager profit♪

826
00:41:04,636 --> 00:41:07,000
♪No matter how hard I try,
it only brings sobs♪

827
00:41:07,147 --> 00:41:11,557
♪Renewing yearly, gone with no return,
teetering, utterly bland♪

828
00:41:26,282 --> 00:41:27,718
♪Leave all behind you♪

829
00:41:27,822 --> 00:41:30,309
♪Gotta go on to better things♪

830
00:41:30,492 --> 00:41:32,621
♪You know how far you've gone♪

831
00:41:32,808 --> 00:41:35,148
♪In the fire you rise again♪

832
00:41:35,216 --> 00:41:37,482
♪You made it through the worst♪

833
00:41:37,842 --> 00:41:39,920
♪The best is yet to come♪

834
00:41:40,169 --> 00:41:42,339
♪The best is yet to come♪

835
00:41:45,040 --> 00:41:46,192
♪Isn't it magical♪

836
00:41:46,192 --> 00:41:49,838
♪All the stars are out tonight♪

837
00:41:49,872 --> 00:41:51,728
♪And I see them sparkling♪

838
00:41:51,952 --> 00:41:54,083
♪Nobody knows♪

839
00:41:54,704 --> 00:41:56,614
♪What tomorrow brings♪

840
00:41:56,880 --> 00:41:59,203
♪You made it through the worst♪

841
00:41:59,390 --> 00:42:01,598
♪The best is yet to come♪

842
00:42:01,885 --> 00:42:04,034
♪The best is yet to come♪

843
00:42:04,330 --> 00:42:05,744
♪Isn't it magical♪

844
00:42:05,744 --> 00:42:07,956
♪Feeling uneasy,
yet no one's chasing me♪

845
00:42:08,030 --> 00:42:10,384
♪Retreating step by step,
everything turning to ash♪

846
00:42:10,384 --> 00:42:11,472
♪I'm silent, I'm roaring♪

847
00:42:11,472 --> 00:42:14,923
♪This helplessness
keeps pushing me towards the cliff♪

848
00:42:15,376 --> 00:42:17,650
♪Trembling legs
carry away a shattered soul♪

849
00:42:18,064 --> 00:42:18,928
♪Who wants to be just a passerby♪

850
00:42:18,928 --> 00:42:20,448
♪Isn't it magical♪
